<br>
I learned my lesson real quick and when I do specs in Oasis, I do it underwater.  I also pull single specs for groups who want to try them out.  Gets to be pretty fun.  I also let everyone there loot the specs now, since I get asked every time I kill one/four.  Same for Sand Giants that are unlucky enough to wander by me.  <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaephire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aephire</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.hawkwoodslegion.com/aephire/images/black_multispot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/18/01 10:20:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Specs and Death</span><hr size=1> I've been quadding spectres in Oasis and OOT.<br>
<br>
Oasis is tougher due to undead adds and those characters that wander too close to get a look.<br>
<br>
OOT is nice and, relatively, deserted. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I normally quad at spec isle but I've pulled them to the AC isle before.  It is definitely easier to quad there with the flat terrain.<br>
<br>
When will these turn green and are there better alternatives for quick exp.? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=klumhru>Klumhru</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/19/01 3:05:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Specs and Death</span><hr size=1> Why did I do OOT 45-49?<br>
<br>
If you lev a bit on the island and take a look at the topography, you'll notice several points on the island that are level with each other. Spires, hills and the flat top of the island. Just kill all the gargoyles till there are only skellys on the island, since the skellys don't aggro, but the gargs always do, all the way up to 49...<br>
<br>
225int + 380mana at the time, I had no problem keeping up with their 6 minute spawn time. I went from 40 to 50 in 8 days, after getting invite to Valhall (My local semiuber guild) when I hit 50. I feel sorry for the nonquading punts.<br>
<br>
Klumhru<br>
