<br>
My original post did mention the situation being hilarious, but I kinda cut that out. =/<br>
<br>
I meant the post to be informative and to make sure that people are careful when doing wizardly things... (near suicidal kites just to get faster-than-hell xp)<br>
<br>
It was funny I guess because i had flashbacks to the first time my brother got his iksar to oasis (8th level) only to be immediately cut down by a spectre at the dock and we spent the next couple hours running him back over again.  THAT was entertainment.  LOL<br>
<br>
Rash <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uibun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ibun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/26/01 6:00:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=184.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Specs and Death</span><hr size=1> I usually quad the oasis spec's in the SW corner, by that little orc camp or whatever and the dwarf npc. I hardly ever see any lowb's around there, only had one instance in 43-44, where lowb's were at the camp, but they didn't aggro. and if there's someone in that area, there's some level &quot;runways&quot; like the one that goes by the sro zone (not that many lowb's there) or a side of a dune south of the inn. Plus it helps to round them up in the water and then bring them straight onto land.<br>
I've also timed the CoF refreshes so that they are, or fraction of a second from, being in range, which is usually about 1-2sec of running straight after casting with sow potion, so I'm able to finish by the time I pass Sro (from the SW corner).<br>
Just my 2cp<br>
<br>
Ibun<br>
44th Ring of Fire<br>
